ffected country or region.\n7. Automated decision-making: The GDPR prohibits businesses from using automated decision-making processes that involve a high degree of risk, such as targeted advertising or predictive profiling.\n8. Privacy by design and default: Companies must consider privacy and data protection principles from the outset in their processing activities, and must take appropriate measures to ensure that personal data is processed in a way that respects individuals' privacy rights.\n9. Data protection impact assessment: Companies must conduct a data protection impact assessment (DPIA) before processing large amounts of personal data. This involves identifying the purposes for which the data will be used, and ensuring that the data is minimized to only what is necessary for those purposes.\n10. Right to erasure: Individuals have the right to request that their personal data be erased if it is no longer necessary for the purpose stated at the time of collection, or if it violates their rights and freedoms.\n\nOverall, the GDPR aims to ensure that businesses handle personal data in an ethical and transparent way, with individuals having greater control over their own data and more protection against unlawful processing practices."}, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'done': True, 'total_duration': 112640153440, 'load_duration': 1417357, 'prompt_eval_count': 1613, 'prompt_eval_duration': 6179080000, 'eval_count': 665, 'eval_duration': 106313403000}